Sequence Information.Peptide Name: CFPS_AMP_19 (cell-free protein synthesis-AMP 19, Phe-rich, AI predicted AMPs)
Sequence Information.Source: AI predicted, machine learning prediction of known protein sequences

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (35.09%) toAMP_14R: 22%; F: 28%.Activity: active against E. coli (MIC 25 uM), B. subtilis (MIC 8.4 uM), A-baumannii clinical strain (MIC >25 uM), Enterobacter spp. (MIC >25 uM), K-pneumoniae DSM 30104 (MIC >25 uM), P-aeruginosa DSM 1117 (MIC >25 uM), S-aureus DSM 11729 MRSA (MIC >25 uM), and E. faecium (MIC 25 uM).Toxicity: Human RBC: HC50>250 uM, not hemo.lytic.

Literature Information.Title: Cell-free biosynthesis combined with deep learning accelerates de novo-development of antimicrobial peptides.
